Cooperative Governance Minister, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma provides details on the revised COVID-19 restrictions following President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address.  JOHANNESBURG - Cooperative Governance Minister, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma provides details on the revised COVID-19 restrictions on Thursday, following President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address. Meanwhile, the Health Department has reported 1,422 new COVID-19 cases. A total of 58 people have died due to the virus, bringing the death toll to 52,846. READ: COVID-19 vaccine: J&J commits 30 million doses for SA The department says recoveries are at 1,474, 319, reflecting a recovery rate of 95%. According to the department says 263,878 healthcare workers are vaccinated.